issue.body: ### Before reporting an issue - [x] I have read and understood the above terms for submitting issues, and I understand that my issue may be closed without action if I do not follow them. ### Area token-exchange ### Describe the bug ## Problem Description When a user is assigned to multiple organizations in KeyCloak, the `organizations` claim is completely missing from the JWT token. ## Environment - **KeyCloak Version**: 26.3.1 - **Organizations Feature**: Enabled (new feature since KeyCloak 24) - **User Assignment**: User is member of 2+ organizations ### Version 26.3.1 ### Regression - [x] The issue is a regression ### Expected behavior JWT token should contain: ```json { "organizations": ["Organization1", "Organization2"], "groups": ["/IT/Admins"], ... } ``` ## Actual Behavior JWT token contains groups but organizations claim is completely missing: ```json { "groups": ["/IT/Admins"], "scope": "openid organization email profile", ... } ``` ### Actual behavior *When user is in multiple organizations:* Organizations claim is completely missing from JWT token: ``` { "groups": ["/IT/Admins"], "scope": "openid organization email profile", "email_verified": true, "name": "XXX", "preferred_username": "XXX" } ``` When user is in single organization: Organizations claim appears correctly: ``` { "organizations": ["SingleOrganization"], "groups": ["/IT/Admins"], "scope": "openid organization email profile", ... } ``` ### How to Reproduce? Please attach screenshots of: 1. **KeyCloak Version** 2. **Organization Mapper Settings**: - Client Scopes ‚Üí organization ‚Üí Mappers ‚Üí Organization Membership - Show all settings (Add to ID token, Add to access token, etc.) 3. **Generated Access Token**: - Client Scopes ‚Üí organization ‚Üí Evaluate ‚Üí [Select User] ‚Üí Generated Access Token - Show the complete token structure 4. **User's Organization Memberships**: - Users ‚Üí [Username] ‚Üí Organizations tab - Show that user is member of multiple organizations ## Related Issues - Similar to GitHub issue about missing organization claims with multiple organizations - This only affects users with 2+ organization memberships - Single organization membership works correctly ## Temporary Workaround Script Mapper can be used as workaround until fix is available. --- 1. 2. 3. 4. ### Anything else? _No response_

pull_request.title: New ChatView: Support incoming updates of messages
pull_request.body:
Use `kMonalUpdatedMessageNotice` for message corrections and MUC message reflections, instead of using `kMonalNewMessageNotice`.

I added observing of this new notification in all the places that are observing `kMonalNewMessageNotice`, except for `MonalAppDelegate`.
I think that's not needed because message updates don't cause the unread counter to be changed.

Also, I'm not sure observing the new notification in `MLContact` is strictly necessary, but it's not harmful.


On a semi-related note, you once said that when posting notifications, `MLNotificationQueue` should always be used (as opposed to `NSNotificationCenter`)
It turns out there are some places in the code base that use `NSNotificationCenter` for posting notifications.
See them with `grep --color=auto -in 'NotificationCenter.*post' Monal/Classes/*.{m,swift}`
Should I use `MLNotificationQueue` in these places?
(The `CFNotificationCenter` ones should remain)

issue.title: Fix QueryJob total_rows attribute error
issue.body:
# Fix QueryJob total_rows attribute error ## Summary This PR fixes a critical `AttributeError` that occurs when the BigQuery API returns a `QueryJob` object without the `total_rows` attribute. The error `'QueryJob' object has no attribute 'total_rows'` was causing the application to crash when users asked questions like "how many republicans are there". **Root Cause:** The BigQuery `QueryJob` object doesn't always populate the `total_rows` attribute, particularly for certain query types (like COUNT queries) or under specific conditions. The code was attempting to access this attribute directly, causing an AttributeError. **Fix:** Changed from direct attribute access `query_job.total_rows` to safe access using `getattr(query_job, 'total_rows', None)`, which returns None if the attribute doesn't exist rather than raising an exception. ## Review & Testing Checklist for Human - [ ] **Critical**: Test end-to-end with actual BigQuery queries that return results (not just permission errors) to verify the fix works and doesn't break normal functionality - [ ] **High**: Verify truncation detection still works correctly when `total_rows` is available vs when it's None - [ ] **Medium**: Test various query types (SELECT, COUNT, aggregations, complex queries) to ensure consistent behavior across different BigQuery response patterns **Recommended Test Plan:** 1. Run the agent CLI with COUNT queries: "how many republicans are there" 2. Run regular SELECT queries to ensure truncation detection still works 3. Try various query patterns to verify no regression in functionality --- ### Diagram ```mermaid %%{ init : { "theme" : "default" }}%% graph TD CLI["app_cli.py"]:::context --> Agent["agent.py"]:::context Agent --> BQTool["bigquery_tool.py"]:::minor-edit BQTool --> BQClient["BigQuery Client"]:::context BQTool --> TotalRowsFix["Safe total_rows access
using getattr()"]:::minor-edit TotalRowsFix --> TruncationLogic["Truncation Detection
Logic"]:::context subgraph Legend L1[Major Edit]:::major-edit L2[Minor Edit]:::minor-edit L3[Context/No Edit]:::context end classDef major-edit fill:#90EE90 classDef minor-edit fill:#87CEEB classDef context fill:#FFFFFF ``` ### Notes - **Testing Limitation**: Due to BigQuery permission constraints in the development environment, I could only verify that error handling works correctly. Full end-to-end testing with successful queries is needed. - **Previous PR Issue**: This fix was supposedly included in PR #57 which shows as "Merged", but the fix didn't make it to main properly, suggesting there may have been a merge issue. - **Change Impact**: Minimal code change (2 lines) but affects a critical path in query result processing. **Session Info**: Requested by Greg (gregtusar@gmail.com) **Link to Devin run**: https://app.devin.ai/sessions/70ba3ae6fc8d46b48eb248b1e5354fd1
